    "narrative": "For today's slate, **Corbin Carroll** leads the squad with an elite efficiency score of 80.12. Despite facing Max Scherzer, **Carroll** benefits from a strong lineup projection and an xwOBA of .372, maintaining his status as our primary ceiling play. Close behind, **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.71) and **James Wood** (71.32) provide significant value; **Soderstrom** benefits from a favorable matchup against Fedde (5.60 xERA) and a 10% park boost, while **Wood** leverages a high-leverage leadoff spot and a 10% order bonus. These three represent the core of our output today, with **Brice Turang** and **Jose Caballero** rounding out our high-efficiency tier, both receiving meaningful boosts from slow opposing pitcher deliveries, which keeps our stolen base potential in play despite the scarcity of the category.\n\nOur most difficult decision fell to **Seiya Suzuki**, who landed on the bench with a 52.23 score. While **Suzuki** offers moderate upside, he was edged out by lower-tier starters who benefited from superior platoon splits or better park factors. Specifically, **Mickey Moniak** (64.30) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (66.30) secured their spots due to more favorable park adjustments and dynamic platoon advantages that outperformed **Suzuki**\u2019s projected output against Peralta. We are also keeping a close watch on the weather; wind blowing in has negatively impacted the projections for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Giancarlo Stanton**, and **Vinnie Pasquantino**, tempering their scores slightly. Additionally, we remain cautious regarding **Luis Campusano** and **Alex Freeland**; as \"Lineup Pending\" status necessitates an assumed #9 spot, both carry an 8% order penalty that forces them into the marginal category. We will monitor official lineups for **Campusano**, **Dalton Rushing**, and **Carroll** closely to ensure these scores remain accurate as first pitch approaches.",
